{
  "stem": "11274.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were with them there, and we were feeding them, and paying them money.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So Mom was cooking for them to whole day.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And-- and this was forbidden.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So the harvest of cutting the greens, and everything, and treating it, and making it into flour was out of the question.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We couldn't do that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But we still planted potatoes.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And Danka and I usually helped with the potato diggings too, sort of for necessity and sort of for fun, that we knew how do it.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So we would-- after the work-- in the fall-- that we did for the Germans, the slave labor, we would go out and take a lantern with us, you know, and-- and-- petrol-- what do you call it?",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The lanterns with us.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And with the lanterns, as long as could through the night.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And then a couple hours sleep, and then in the morning go again for slave work.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So we dug out all the potatoes, and Father-- Father would come with a wagon and with-- or with the sacks, and we had the potatoes in a potato cellar.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then-- this is all we could have, so if we needed flour or something, we had to buy.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So Danka and I started sewing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She learned a little bit sewing from Zosia and I, because Zosia wasn't home anymore.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "When she was home, she was earning some money, and she was-- she was helping because we were all one family waiting together.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "One day, I remember, there was a really short on-- on flour, and there was a little piece of bread like this on the table.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And Mom-- Mom gave-- gave it to me, and I gave it to Danka, Danka gave it back to Dad, and Dad gave it back to Mom.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
